description: Vermont’s crown jewel for mountain biking with over 100 miles of smooth, fast singletrack.

name: Cannon Mountain
description: Located in Franconia Notch State Park, Cannon Mountain is a state-owned ski area.

name: Attitash Mountain Resort
description: Attitash Mountain Resort spans two peaks—Attitash and Bear Peak—and offers skiing, snowboarding, and summer mountain biking. Known for its terrain parks, alpine slide, and year-round family activities.

name: Jasper National Park
description: Largest national park in the Canadian Rockies, featuring vast wilderness, Columbia Icefield, Athabasca Glacier, and a UNESCO Dark Sky Preserve. Less crowded than Banff with exceptional stargazing.

name: Pacific Rim National Park Reserve
description: West Coast paradise featuring Long Beach, the famous West Coast Trail, rainforest, and excellent surfing, kayaking, and whale watching opportunities. Rich Nuu-chah-nulth First Nation culture.

name: Gros Morne National Park
description: UNESCO World Heritage Site featuring dramatic fjords, the Tablelands (exposed Earth's mantle), coastal lowlands, and ancient geological formations. Stunning mountain and ocean scenery.

name: Palenque National Park
description: Home to ancient Maya ruins surrounded by lush jungle, waterfalls, and wildlife. A UNESCO World Heritage Site.

name: Sumidero Canyon National Park
description: Dramatic canyon carved by the Grijalva River, with towering cliffs, boat tours, and rich biodiversity.

name: Izta-Popo Zoquiapan National Park
description: Covers two iconic volcanoes—Popocatépetl and Iztaccíhuatl—with alpine trails, panoramic views, and high-altitude ecosystems.

name: Cabo Pulmo National Park
description: Marine park with one of the oldest coral reefs in North America. Ideal for snorkeling, diving, and eco-tourism.

name: Sian Ka’an Biosphere Reserve
description: UNESCO site with mangroves, lagoons, tropical forests, and Mayan ruins. Offers kayaking, birdwatching, and eco-lodging.
